"956","<p style=margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:22.3pt;margin-top:0in;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;line-height:13.8pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"957","<p style=margin-bottom:13.9pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;line-height:13.8pt;>In planning and performing our audits of the"
"958","financial statements of Dreyfus/Standish Fixed Income Fund, Dreyfus/Standish"
"959","Global Fixed Income Fund and Dreyfus/Standish International Fixed Income Fund,"
"960","each a series of Dreyfus Investment Funds (collectively, the &#8220;Funds&#8221;) as of and"
"961","for the year ended December 31, 2011, in accordance with the standards of the"
"962","Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we considered their"
"963","internal control over financial reporting, including controls over safeguarding"
"964","securities, as a basis for designing our auditing procedures for the purpose of"
"965","expressing our opinion on the financial statements and to comply with the"
"966","requirements of Form N-SAR, but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion on"
"967","the effectiveness of the Funds&#8217; internal control over financial reporting."
"968","Accordingly, we express no such opinion. </font></p>"
"969","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;>Management of the Funds is"
"970","responsible for establishing and maintaining effective internal control over"
"971","financial reporting.&#160; In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates and"
"972","judgments by management are required to assess the expected benefits and"
"973","related costs of controls.&#160; A fund&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting"
"974","is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability"
"975","of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external"
"976","purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles (GAAP). A"
"977","fund's internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and"
"978","procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable"
"979","detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the"
"980","assets of the fund; (2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are"
"981","recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in"
"982","accordance with GAAP, and that receipts and expenditures of the fund are being"
"983","made only in accordance with authorizations of management and trustees of the"
"984","fund; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely"
"985","detection of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition of the fund's assets"
"986","that could have a material effect on the financial statements.</font></p>"
"987","<p style=margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;line-height:13.8pt;>&nbsp;</font></p>"
"988","<p style=margin-bottom:13.9pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;line-height:13.8pt;>Because of its inherent limitations, internal"
"989","control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also,"
"990","projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject to"
"991","the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions,"
"992","or that the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may"
"993","deteriorate. </font></p>"
"994","<p style=margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;><font color=black face=Times New Roman lang=EN-US style=font-size:12.0pt;>A deficiency in internal control"
"995","over financial reporting exists when the design or operation of a control does"
"996","not allow management or employees, in the normal course of performing their"
"997","assigned functions, to prevent or detect misstatements on a timely basis.</font></p>"
